## v1.3.0 (2026-05-18)

**Changed by:** ProjectMnemosyne skill-corpus consolidation session — Mojo sub-PR 4/4 (M3 series) silent-success pattern surfaced; re-dispatch created duplicate PR #1812
**Verification:** verified-local

### What changed

- Added new "When to Use" trigger (#6): sub-agent goes silent without returning final message — query branch before re-dispatching
- Added new `### Pre-dispatch check: verify the agent didn't already succeed silently` sub-section under Verified Workflow with decision table
- Extended Quick Reference with `gh pr list --head <branch>` as STEP 0 before any re-dispatch
- Added new Failed Attempts row: silent Sonnet sub-agent (Mojo sub-PR 4/4) re-dispatched without branch check → created duplicate PR #1812 (closed as dup of #1811)
- Added new Verified On row: HomericIntelligence/ProjectMnemosyne 2026-05-18 (#1813 consolidation; #1812 duplicate catch)
- Extended description with trigger (6) for silent-success pattern
- Bumped to v1.3.0

### Why

v1.2.0 covered four failure shapes: GitHub-state mismatch, commit-content corruption, artifact confabulation, and hallucinated tool restriction. All four assume the agent produces some output (prose or artifact). This session surfaced a fifth: **silent-success** — the agent completes its entire workflow but never returns a final-message text. The orchestrator interprets silence as failure and re-dispatches. The fix is to query GitHub by the deterministic branch name before any re-dispatch. This generalizes trust-but-verify from "verify what the agent claims" to "verify what the agent should have done, whether or not it claims it."

